  "prompt": "How do I deal with extreme confusion, pain & helplessness after being completely cut off by my S.O, who doesn't want any type of contact ever?",
  "response": "Dealing with sudden relationship loss can be incredibly difficult. Here are some supportive steps:\n\n1. Allow yourself to grieve\n- Accept your emotions are valid\n- Don't suppress your pain\n- Understand healing takes time\n\n2. Seek support\n- Talk to trusted friends/family\n- Consider professional counseling\n- Join support groups\n\n3. Self-care practices\n- Maintain basic health routines\n- Exercise regularly\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Eat nutritious meals\n- Practice mindfulness/meditation\n\n4. Emotional processing\n- Journal your feelings\n- Avoid obsessive rumination\n- Don't blame yourself\n- Recognize you can't control their actions\n\n5. Practical steps\n- Block communication channels if needed\n- Remove reminders/triggers\n- Focus on personal growth\n- Develop new interests/hobbies\n\n6. Long-term healing\n- Rebuild self-esteem\n- Work on personal boundaries\n- Consider therapy for deeper emotional work\n- Stay open to future connections\n\n7. Perspective shifts\n- Understand this isn't your fault\n- Recognize this as an opportunity for personal transformation\n- Believe in your ability to heal\n\nRemember: You're stronger than you realize, and healing is possible. Be patient and compassionate with yourself.\n\nWould you like to discuss any specific aspect of your situation?",
